summary:
Rwanda-backed rebels overran Congolese troops and entered Goma, a city in eastern Democratic Republic of Congo. United Nations reports state over 1 million people displaced within the aid hub city amid gunfire and shelling. This follows clashes displacing hundreds of thousands previously; aid agencies expect worsened humanitarian crisis with impacts on Central African stability and refugee flows to neighboring countries.

In the Middle East, Israel permitted displaced Palestinians to cross a bisecting military zone on foot into northern Gaza after a hostage release ended a deadlock. Hundreds of thousands of displaced residents are affected. Separately, Israeli military confirmed a strike killed three Lebanese journalists including Ali Shoeib of Hezbollah-linked Al Manar Television in southern Lebanon. Iranian attacks injured workers at major aluminum sites in the United Arab Emirates and Bahrain, disrupting production at facilities previously struck.

NATO launched its first coordinated response to suspected sabotage after another deep-sea cable severance in the Baltic Sea. SpaceX launched Crew-10 with four astronauts including two from NASA from Kennedy Space Center on Friday to relieve Butch Wilmore and Suni Williams stuck on the International Space Station for nine months; the craft docked Saturday. China resumed regular Beijing-Pyongyang flights with Air China Boeing 737 service after six years, following train restoration. Kenya reported 110 flood deaths across 30 counties from ongoing rains, displacing thousands as government coordinates relief. China's Vanke reported massive losses amid property sector troubles."}
